<TITLE> President, PM, others get hefty pay hike </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 8 (bdnews24.com)The cabinet on Monday approved a pay hike of up to 83 percent for the president, prime minister, speaker, chief justice, ministers, and Supreme Court judges, among other top officials. Under the new pay scale, the president's monthly salary will jump from Tk 33,400 to Tk 61,200 and the prime minister's will go up from Tk 32,000 to Tk 58,600, the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told a briefing after the weekly cabinet meeting. The speaker will get a raise from Tk 31,000 to Tk 57,200. The salary of the chief justice will be hiked from Tk 30,500 to Tk 56,000. Salaries of the ministers will go up from Tk 29,000 to Tk 53,100, as will the deputy speaker's. State ministers will climb from Tk 26,100 to 47,800 and deputy ministers from Tk 24,650 to Tk 45,150. Appellate Division judges will see a raise from Tk 29,000 to Tk 53,100 and High Court judges from Tk 27,000 to Tk 47,000. The monthly salary of the MPs will be hiked from Tk 15,000 to Tk 27,500. The raises come in line with last year's 83 percent hike in civil service pay. b
